'''Jasmin Werner XXX''' (5031-5115) is a Canadian-British forensic scientist and convicted murderer.

== Early life (5031-5053) ==
Werner was born in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan. She was the youngest of three children born to [[Eberhard Werner XXIX]] and his ex-girlfriend Ellen Singh.

In 5037, Werner enrolled at Little Poirot Primary School.

In 5043, Werner enrolled at St. Chichi’s Middle School.

In 5046, Werner enrolled at Henri Dube Secondary School.

In 5049, Werner enrolled at the University of Saskatchewan.

== Career (5053-5071) ==
In 5053, Werner became a crime scene technician for the Saskatoon Police Service.

In 5059, Werner was promoted to forensic investigator.

In 5071, Werner resigned. She emigrated to Guayaquil, Ecuador.

== Life in Ecuador (5071-5075) ==
In 5072, Werner installed X.

== Prison sentence (5075-5097) ==
In 5075, Werner emigrated to Blackpool, England. She was convicted of murdering her second husband, Jesse Statham, and was sentenced to 47 years in prison. She appealed the sentence to the Court of Appeal, Criminal Division, and her sentence was reduced to 27 years. She served her sentence at Blackpool Max Security Prison.

In 5097, Werner was released on licence.

== Death ==
In 5115, Werner died of a stroke. Her stepdaughter, Kate, attended her funeral.

== Marriage, relationships, and children ==
From 5041 to 5047, Werner dated a student named Alex Pelletier (5031-after 5097).

From 5047 to 5048, Werner dated a student named Adam Watson (5031-after 5097). They had a daughter, Jasmin Werner XXXI (5048-5129).

In 5059, Werner had one night stands with five unemployed men, Justin Bennett (5041-after 5097), Noah Champion (5041-after 5097), Hunter Cummings (5041-after 5097), Arnaud Love (5041-after 5097), and Lawrence Perry (5041-after 5097).

From 5059 to 5075, Werner and Champion were married. They had 13 children, Ella (5067-5154), Sonny (5068-5150), Eli (5069-5133), Maude (5070-5153), Victor (5071-5158), Jilly (5072-5164), Rosalie (5072-5154), Aria (5074-5155), Dick (5074-5154), Dickie (5074-5146), Michelle (5074-5151), Nina (5074-5155), and BJ Champion (5075-5160).

In 5075, Werner married Jesse Statham (5024-5075). She had a stepson, Finley (5062-5136), from Statham’s prior marriage to a woman named Heidi Foster, and two stepchildren, Theo (5066-5137) and [[Kate Statham]], from Statham’s prior marriage to a woman named Amelia Seaman.

Werner has two twin sons, Landon (5075-5077) and Leo Werner (5075-5138), who were conceived via artificial insemination.
